race.comment: Sticking with the progressive GALWAY SHAWL (4). Was a debut winner here at the 1000m then stayed that trip last time at Belmont Park and ran on late to finish fifth. Looks suited out in journey now and hard to beat this line-up. ZIPPY ZANY (1) is fairly consistent and looks a danger. Close-up fifth over further two back then beaten a nose last time at Northam over 1300m. Has the claim and will be on speed. ROSIE CAN RUN (7) doesn't win out of turn and might want further but has the ability to run well here fresh. Hasn't raced since being tested in the Listed Belmont Oaks. Has run some good races this trip and expected to be winding up hard. MA MA BELLE (5) raced on speed fresh and finished fifth in a fair return. Fitter for it and can do much better. SANCTIONS (2) gave a sight fresh then weakened in the same race as GALWAY SHAWL. Fitter again and can give a sight.
